+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Classified all visible review threads from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing code. Applied changes only for the three actionable threads: `T-214-01`, `T-214-04`, and `T-214-05`.
+
+## Thread Classification
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated hunk
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+## Changes Made
+
+- `src/policy/preview.py`
+  Added local approval-state normalization and preserved `approval_state` plus `requires_human_review` in the fallback payload.
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+  Normalized the approval state before building the preview payload so router callers do not leak `manual_review`.
+- `tests/test_preview.py`
+  Extended the writable preview regression surface to cover `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md`
+  Updated the fallback example to show the corrected normalized payload.
+
+## Behavior Confirmed
+
+`build_policy_preview(request_id="req-214", approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, actor="review-bot")` now yields a fallback payload with:
+
+```json
+{
+  "request_id": "req-214",
+  "status": "preview_unavailable",
+  "actor": "review-bot",
+  "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+  "requires_human_review": true
+}
+```
+
+## Verification
+
+Ran:
+
+```bash
+python -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result: `OK` (4 tests passed).
