+## Review Reply Draft
+
+### T-214-01
+Addressed in `src/policy/preview.py`. The fallback payload now preserves the normalized `approval_state` and includes `requires_human_review`, so downstream consumers see the same approval contract even when `preview_enabled=False`.
+
+### T-214-02
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. This thread reports the same reopened fallback regression, so no separate code change was applied.
+
+### T-214-03
+Marked obsolete. The suggestion targets an outdated diff hunk and would reintroduce legacy preview branching that is not part of the current branch contract, so it was intentionally not applied.
+
+### T-214-04
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added fallback regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` and asserted normalization to `human_review_required` plus `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+### T-214-05
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback example now includes `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`, matching the corrected runtime payload.
